article.headline: Kennesaw State 77, North Florida 57
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Ronnell Wooten hit a 3-pointer and a layup to cap a 9-0 second-half run that Kennesaw State used to break open a close game en route to a 77-57 victory over North Florida on Monday. Wooten, who finished with 17 points to lead the Owls (8-12, 4-4 Atlantic Sun Conference), hit the 3-pointer to make it 47-40 with 15:17 to play, then rebounded a missed jumper by Kennesaw's Golden Ingle and put it in 50 seconds later for a 49-40 lead. North Florida's Chris Timberlake hit a 3-pointer to make it 49-43 but that was as close as the Ospreys (2-15, 0-7) would get. Kennesaw pulled away and led by 22 points, 72-50, with 4:58 left. The Owls led for most of the first half and were ahead 37-33 at intermission, but North Florida came back to tie it at 40 on Aaron Carruthers' 3-pointer at 17:43. Shaun Stegall had 14 points and 11 rebounds for Kennesaw. Brent Ragsdale added 13 points and Ingle 11. James Grimball led North Florida with 17 points and 12 rebounds, while Carruthers scored 14.
